<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id905479a0-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s3985"><num value="3985">§ 3985.</num><heading> Temporary details</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A period of duty of not more than six months in duration by a member of the Service shall be considered a temporary detail and shall not be considered an assignment within the meaning of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id905479a1-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/465/tI/s505">Pub. L. 96–465, title I, § 505</ref>, <date date="1980-10-17">Oct. 17, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/2094">94 Stat. 2094</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
